<subSubSection id="99F2651FFFBAFFE0FF1CFECE4861FA7E" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D1573694FFBAFFE0FF1CFECE4BDEFC9E" blockId="11.[113,767,279,1423]" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBAFFE0FF1CFECE4987FEDE" box="[151,229,280,303]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">Notes. –</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFBAFFE0FF60FEC148DDFEDE" author="BURMAN" box="[235,447,279,303]" firstAuthor="BURMAN" journalOrPublisher="Amsterdam" page="232" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" refId="ref8940" refString="BURMAN, N. L. (1768). Flora Indica: cui accedit series zoophytorum indicorum, nec non prodromus florae capensis. Amsterdam." title="Flora Indica: cui accedit series zoophytorum indicorum, nec non prodromus florae capensis" type="book" year="1768">BURMAN (1768: 232)</bibRefCitation>
cited in the protologue several plates and two 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBAFFE0FE96FEEE483FFEBE" box="[285,349,312,335]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">Pryon</emphasis>
collections from 
<collectingCountry id="A9FF7604FFBAFFE0FDA8FEE14BF2FEBE" box="[547,656,311,335]" name="Indonesia" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
(“ 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBAFFE0FD26FEE14852FE9E" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">malaice fimbar-minganang</emphasis>
” and (semicolon!) “ 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBAFFE0FE70FE8E4B87FE9E" box="[507,741,343,367]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">javanice daun sambang</emphasis>
”). The 
<specimenCount id="C7EEFD1DFFBAFFE0FF2BFEA1484AFE7E" box="[160,296,375,399]" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" type="generic" typeStatus="syntypes">two syntypes</specimenCount>
are extant in G-PREL. One bear the Malay name “ 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBAFFE0FF35FE4148E1FE5E" box="[190,387,407,431]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">fimbar-minganang</emphasis>
” from Pryon’s hand [
<collectionCode id="B7F9AE51FFBAFFE0FDE1FE414B1CFE5E" box="[618,638,407,431]" country="Switzerland" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15706" name="Conservatoire et Jardin botaniques de la Ville de Genève" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" type="Herbarium">G</collectionCode>
00360042] and represents a fertile specimen with a mature fern leaf. The second collection bears the Javanese name “ 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBAFFE0FDA5FE014BDFFE1E" box="[558,701,471,495]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">daun sambang</emphasis>
” from the same hand [
<collectionCode id="B7F9AE51FFBAFFE0FE9EFE21484AFDFE" box="[277,296,503,527]" country="Switzerland" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15706" name="Conservatoire et Jardin botaniques de la Ville de Genève" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" type="Herbarium">G</collectionCode>
00360110] and represents a sterile specimen, probably collected in 
<collectingRegion id="132CF876FFBAFFE0FEC4FDC14819FDDF" box="[335,379,535,558]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">Java</collectingRegion>
. An uncited 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBAFFE0FE74FDC14BF6FDDE" box="[511,660,535,559]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">Paul Hermann</emphasis>
specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="A9FF7604FFBAFFE0FF25FDE1499CFDBE" box="[174,254,567,591]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">Ceylon</collectingCountry>
extant in the library of the Institut de 
<collectingCountry id="A9FF7604FFBAFFE0FD3AFDE14B99FDBF" box="[689,763,567,590]" name="France" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">France</collectingCountry>
in Paris (BIF-CEYL p. 41) (
<figureCitation id="49D32A11FFBAFFE0FE3DFD814899FD9E" box="[438,507,599,623]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[136,164,1914,1933]" captionTargetBox="[339,1271,276,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-18@12.[339,1271,276,1863]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 6. – Page 41 of Paul Hermann’s herbarium from Ceylon in BIF-CEYL with original material of Polypodium scolopendria Burm. f. [© Bibliothèque de l’Institut de France, Paris]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5684546" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5684546/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) may also be regarded as original material; it was used by 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFBAFFE0FE71FDA14BC4FD7E" author="BURMAN" box="[506,678,631,655]" firstAuthor="BURMAN" journalOrPublisher="Amsterdam" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" refId="ref8920" refString="BURMAN, J. (1737). Thesaurus Zeylanicus, exhibens plantas in insula Zeylana nascentes. Amsterdam." title="Thesaurus Zeylanicus, exhibens plantas in insula Zeylana nascentes" type="book" year="1737">BURMAN (1737)</bibRefCitation>
’s father for his 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBAFFE0FF4AFD4148FCFD5E" box="[193,414,663,687]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">Thesaurus Zeylanicus</emphasis>
, a work cited in the protologue (see above Notes under 
<taxonomicName id="16E84D17FFBAFFE0FEF7FD614B2BFD3E" box="[380,585,695,719]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Polypodiaceae" genus="Polypodium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acutum">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBAFFE0FEF7FD614B2BFD3E" box="[380,585,695,719]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">Polypodium acutum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="16E84D17FFBAFFE0FD0AFD6E4B8FFD3E" box="[641,749,695,719]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Polypodiaceae" genus="Polypodium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="palustre">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBAFFE0FD0AFD6E4B8FFD3E" box="[641,749,695,719]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">P. palustre</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFBAFFE0FFFAFD01482DFD1E" author="MERRILL" box="[113,335,727,751]" firstAuthor="MERRILL" journalOrPublisher="Philippine J. Sci." page="335" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" pagination="329 - 388" part="19" refId="ref9969" refString="MERRILL, E. D. (1921). A review of the new species of plants proposed by N. L. Burman in his Flora Indica. Philippine J. Sci. 19: 329 - 388." title="A review of the new species of plants proposed by N. L. Burman in his Flora Indica" type="journal article" year="1921">MERRILL (1921: 335)</bibRefCitation>
made a clear reference to “ 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBAFFE0FDF8FD014BD9FD1F" box="[627,699,727,750]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">Pryon’s</emphasis>
Javan specimen for which the local name 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBAFFE0FE78FD214BE6FCFE" box="[499,644,759,783]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">daun sembang</emphasis>
is cited” as “actual type”. This should be considered as an implicit lectotypification, despite the fact that the 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBAFFE0FD94FCE14B17FCBE" box="[543,629,823,847]" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">selected</emphasis>
specimen is unfortunately the sterile one (G-PREL [
<collectionCode id="B7F9AE51FFBAFFE0FDA8FC814B55FC9E" box="[547,567,855,879]" country="Switzerland" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15706" name="Conservatoire et Jardin botaniques de la Ville de Genève" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" type="Herbarium">G</collectionCode>
00360110]).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1573694FFBAFFE0FF1CFCA14B7BFB5E" blockId="11.[113,767,279,1423]" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFBAFFE0FF1CFCA148D3FC7E" author="HOVENKAMP" box="[151,433,887,911]" editor="PARRIS, B. S." firstAuthor="HOVENKAMP" page="159" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" pagination="97 - 198" part="2" refId="ref9600" refString="HOVENKAMP, P. H. (2013 b). 39. Polypodiaceae. In: PARRIS, B. S. et al. (ed.), Fl. Penins. Malaysia ser. 1, 2: 97 - 198." title="Polypodiaceae" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Fl. Penins. Malaysia" year="2013" yearSuffix="b">HOVENKAMP (2013b: 159)</bibRefCitation>
cited “ 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBAFFE0FE75FCA14BADFC7E" box="[510,719,887,911]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">Herb. Hermann s.n.</emphasis>
, 
<collectingCountry id="A9FF7604FFBAFFE0FD50FCA149D5FC5E" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
[
<collectingCountry id="A9FF7604FFBAFFE0FF4EFC414879FC5E" box="[197,283,919,943]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">Ceylon</collectingCountry>
] (n.v.)” as type, but first selected an uncited specimen, and second failed to mention the institution of deposit and the term 
<typeStatus id="0E538836FFBAFFE0FED1FC0148DEFC1E" box="[346,444,983,1007]" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">lectotype</typeStatus>
to effect the lectotypification (
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFBAFFE0FFF0FC21480DFBFE" author="TURLAND" box="[123,367,1015,1039]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="TURLAND" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" refId="ref10318" refString="TURLAND, N. J., J. H. WIERSEMA, F. R. BARRIE, W. GREUTER, D. L. HAWKSWORTH, P. S. HERENDEEN, S. KNAPP, W. - H. KUSBER, D. - Z. LI, K. MARHOLD, T. W. MAY, J. MCNEILL, A. M. MONRO, J. PRADO, M. J. PRICE &amp; G. F. SMITH (2018). International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Veg. 159." title="International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017" type="proceedings" year="2018">TURLAND et al., 2018</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 9.12, 9.22, 9.23). 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFBAFFE0FDF8FC214982FBDE" author="VERDCOURT" editor="BEENTJE, H. J." firstAuthor="VERDCOURT" page="24" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" refId="ref10363" refString="VERDCOURT, B. (2001). Polypodiaceae. In: BEENTJE, H. J. (ed.), Fl. Trop. E. Africa." title="Polypodiaceae" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Fl. Trop. E. Africa" year="2001">VERDCOURT (2001: 24)</bibRefCitation>
cited as 
<typeStatus id="0E538836FFBAFFE0FECFFBC148C9FBDE" box="[324,427,1047,1071]" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">lectotype</typeStatus>
: “ 
<collectingCountry id="A9FF7604FFBAFFE0FE4BFBC1489EFBDE" box="[448,508,1047,1071]" name="India" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="A9FF7604FFBAFFE0FD83FBC14B17FBDE" box="[520,629,1047,1071]" name="Indonesia" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion id="132CF876FFBAFFE0FD09FBC14BD2FBDF" box="[642,688,1047,1070]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">Java</collectingRegion>
, 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBAFFE0FD37FBCE49F7FBBE" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">Pryon s.n.</emphasis>
(
<collectionCode id="B7F9AE51FFBAFFE0FF2FFBE149D9FBBE" box="[164,187,1079,1103]" country="Switzerland" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15706" name="Conservatoire et Jardin botaniques de la Ville de Genève" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" type="Herbarium">G</collectionCode>
, lecto)”. In a footnote, he accepted Schelpe (
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFBAFFE0FD10FBE1480EFB9E" author="SCHELPE &amp; ANTHONY" editor="LEISTNER, O. A." firstAuthor="SCHELPE" page="165" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" refId="ref10190" refString="SCHELPE, E. A. C. L. E. &amp; N. C. ANTHONY (1986). Pteridophyta, Polypodiaceae. In: LEISTNER, O. A. (ed.), Fl. S. Africa." title="Pteridophyta, Polypodiaceae" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Fl. S. Africa" year="1986">SCHELPE &amp; ANTHONY, 1986: 165</bibRefCitation>
)’s citation of a specimen he had seen (“Type: 
<collectingCountry id="A9FF7604FFBAFFE0FF41FBA14867FB7E" box="[202,261,1143,1167]" name="India" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">India</collectingCountry>
, Herb. Burmann (
<collectionCode id="B7F9AE51FFBAFFE0FE46FBA14886FB7E" box="[461,484,1143,1167]" country="Switzerland" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15706" name="Conservatoire et Jardin botaniques de la Ville de Genève" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" type="Herbarium">G</collectionCode>
, holo!)”), but Schelpe did not designate a single specimen as type.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1573694FFBAFFE0FF1CFB614B6CFAFE" blockId="11.[113,767,279,1423]" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFBAFFE0FF1CFB61483DFB3E" author="KNAPP" box="[151,351,1207,1231]" firstAuthor="KNAPP" journalOrPublisher="Gaoshu Township" page="122" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" refId="ref9684" refString="KNAPP, R. (2014). Index to Ferns and Fern Allies of Taiwan. Gaoshu Township." title="Index to Ferns and Fern Allies of Taiwan" type="book" year="2014">KNAPP (2014: 122)</bibRefCitation>
cited a 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBAFFE0FE3DFB6E4896FB3E" box="[438,500,1208,1231]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">Pryon</emphasis>
specimen at 
<collectionCode id="B7F9AE51FFBAFFE0FD08FB614BFBFB3E" box="[643,665,1207,1231]" country="Switzerland" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15706" name="Conservatoire et Jardin botaniques de la Ville de Genève" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" type="Herbarium">Gas</collectionCode>
<typeStatus id="0E538836FFBAFFE0FD36FB6149FDFB1E" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">lectotype</typeStatus>
(“ 
<collectingCountry id="A9FF7604FFBAFFE0FF33FB014991FB1E" box="[184,243,1239,1263]" name="India" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion id="132CF876FFBAFFE0FF76FB01484BFB1F" box="[253,297,1239,1262]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">Java</collectingRegion>
, 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBAFFE0FEBFFB0E48FEFB1E" box="[308,412,1240,1263]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">Pryon s.n.</emphasis>
(LT: 
<collectionCode id="B7F9AE51FFBAFFE0FE5CFB01488FFB1E" box="[471,493,1239,1263]" country="Switzerland" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15706" name="Conservatoire et Jardin botaniques de la Ville de Genève" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" type="Herbarium">G</collectionCode>
) // 
<collectingCountry id="A9FF7604FFBAFFE0FD9CFB014BE3FB1E" box="[535,641,1239,1263]" name="Indonesia" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
”) but again without referring to a single specimen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1573694FFBAFFE0FF1CFAC14861FA7E" blockId="11.[113,767,279,1423]" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">
<taxonomicName id="16E84D17FFBAFFE0FF1CFAC148C1FADE" box="[151,419,1303,1327]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Polypodiaceae" genus="Phymatosorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scolopendria">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFBAFFE0FF1CFAC148C1FADE" box="[151,419,1303,1327]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="104">Phymatosorus scolopendria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a common fern in the tropics of the Old World. Its native range is mainly restricted to the Malesian region, and maybe a few adjacent areas (
<collectionCode id="B7F9AE51FFBAFFE0FD19FA814BCAFA9E" box="[658,680,1367,1391]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15406" name="Harvard University - Arnold Arboretum" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" type="Herbarium">A</collectionCode>
. Smith, pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
